pullRequest.body:
The commits below are all approved PRs, as planned, except:
* the second last one which resolves conflicts in `lake-manifest.json` and `lean-toolchain`.
* the last one the reverts a mysterious change in `Mathlib.Analysis.Seminorm`, discussed in the comment below.

---

(I don't understand how those conflicts were still there after #8779, but I'm not going to wait to find out!)

nodes.body: There were some unexpected changes in `Mathlib.Analysis.Seminorm`, and I don't understand how they've ended up on this branch. I have reverted them in [d0b37f2](https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/pull/8781/commits/d0b37f22e6f5c27050563846b0ec5b19ed5efcc0), and posted about them on [zulip](https://leanprover.zulipchat.com/#narrow/stream/287929-mathlib4/topic/bump.2Fv4.2E4.2E0/near/405463026) if anyone wants to recover it.
